‘Hymnus Sancti Conrgilli Abbatis nostri! This is an alphabetical Hymn of twenty-three stanzas, to which an introductory stanza has been prefixed. Each stanza consists of eight lines, except the second stanza which consists of ten lines The metre is iambic dimeter acatalectic. Every line in almost every stanza either begins, or ends, or both begins and ends with the same letter. It was impossible to carry out this principle in its contpleteness throughout a long Hymn, but it has been carried out toan extent which leaves it still a very remarkable tour deferre.
